Privacy Policy Disclosure
As our customer, you provide us with your personal information. We use that information to administer your account, inform you about your energy and water usage, and manage, provide, and improve our safe, reliable, and cost-efficient services and operations.
We want you to have trust and confidence in the protection of your personal information. We do not sell or rent personal information about our customers. We do not disclose information about you, except as necessary to perform our utility business operations, sometimes with the help of vendors or business partners, or as permitted by law.
We are committed to protecting customer privacy. We take precautions to protect customer's information. We secure our buildings, verify your identity when you call or visit us, place firewalls around our computer network, and limit employee access to your personal information. We also require vendors and business partners to safeguard information they receive from us.
Colorado Springs Utilities offers customers a variety of ways to communicate with us. However, when sensitive information is to be discussed, we encourage our customers to communicate from secure locations using secure tools (email, social media, and cell phones are generally not secure tools).
We constantly strive to improve our business practices. Therefore, from time to time, we may communicate with you about steps we have taken to enhance the security of your personal information, and may ask for your cooperation in implementing certain procedures and safeguards.
