Cookies Policy
Definitions
“Cookies” means small files that are placed on Your computer, mobile device or any other device by a website, containing details of your browsing history on that website among its many uses.
“Website” refers to the website of Colorado Springs Utilities, accessible from CSU.org.
“You” means the individual accessing or using the Website, a company, or any legal entity on behalf of which such individual is accessing or using the Website, as applicable.
Policy
Cookies are small files placed on your device to store data that can be recalled by a web server or website. We use cookies and similar technologies for storing and honoring your settings, enabling you to sign in, providing interest-based advertising, combating fraud, analyzing how our products and website perform, and other legitimate purposes.
CSU may use cookies, web beacons, and other technologies designed to show you ads and content based on your activities on our websites. These technologies may be used to better understand how you and others use our websites so that improvements can be made to our products and services. These technologies may also be used to perform essential website functions and analysis.
You have a variety of tools to control the data collected by cookies and the CSU website. For example, you can use controls in your internet browser to limit how the websites you visit are able to use cookies and to withdraw your consent by clearing or blocking cookies. You may also opt out of Cookies directly on the CSU website. CSU does not store sensitive personal information, such as mailing addresses, account passwords, etc., in the Cookies we use.
If You prefer to avoid the use of Cookies on the Website, You must disable the use of Cookies in your browser and then delete the Cookies saved in your browser associated with this website. You may use this option for preventing the use of Cookies at any time. If You do not accept Our Cookies, You may experience some inconvenience in your use of the Website and some features may not function properly. For further help, please visit the help pages of your web browser.
